reviewText: The content was very scattered and many things were vague and not explained, and this caused confusion and confusion for the learner's mind. So that the student should understand the meaning of many specialized words by searching the internet. there were too many professors and each of them presented some points and also there was no imagine of the professor while teaching, which made it seem a bit boring. Also, the volume of uploaded videos was very high, while it would be better if the number of videos were more but if volume was smaller. this course had many weaknesses, but also I learned a lot from this course and appreciate it.

This is an excellent, intensive and well-curated overview on the state-of-the-art (as of this writing) thinking and findings on extracellular vesicles as part of the internal biological milieu. The material provides a sober view of the current activities, potentials and challenges in the field. As with the preceding course (Basics of Extracellular Vesicles), I will highly recommend this offering to those with college-level grasp of cell & molecular biology, biochemistry and/or biophysics who may be interested to work in this exciting field. The videos are considerably long, so future takers with the necessary background should devote bouts of undivided attention to finish the lectures.Those planning to build a career in this discipline will find themselves in the company and guidance of a highly-coordinated international community of scientists who developed this course.
